The paper deals with the reconfiguration graph of colourings of a graph, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The focus is on planar graphs, which suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of determining the diameter of the reconfiguration graph is a fundamental question in the study of graph colourings, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.GT) and combinatorics (cs.CC).
